{{Infobox Ethnic group |group = Mal Paharia |image = |pop = |popplace = {{flag|India}} |region1 = [[Jharkhand]] |pop1 = 135,797 (2011 census) |ref1 = <ref name="census">{{Cite web|url=http://www.censusindia.gov.in/2011census/PCA/ST.html|title=A-11 Individual Scheduled Tribe Primary Census Abstract Data and its Appendix|publisher=Office of the Registrar General & Census Commissioner, India|website=www.censusindia.gov.in|access-date=2017-11-18}}</ref> |region2 = [[West Bengal]] |pop2 = 44,538 |region3 = [[Bihar]] |pop3 = 2,225 |languages = [[Mal Paharia language]]{{*}}[[Bengali language|Bengali]] |religions = [[Hinduism]], traditional beliefs |related = }}
The '''Mal Paharia''' people are a tribal people of [[West Bengal]], [[Bihar]] and [[Jharkhand]] in [[India]].<ref name="anagrasarkalyan">{{cite web|title=Scheduled Tribe List Of West Bengal State |url=http://www.anagrasarkalyan.gov.in/htm/st_list.html |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090829121426/http://anagrasarkalyan.gov.in/htm/st_list.html |dead-url=yes |archive-date=2009-08-29 |accessdate= |date= |website=anagrasarkalyan.gov.in }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Bihar Scheduled Tribe List |url= http://tribesindia.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=126&Itemid=104&lang=en|accessdate=|date= |website =tribesindia.com}}</ref> They are listed as a Scheduled Tribe by the governments of West Bengal, Bihar and Jharkhand.<ref name="anagrasarkalyan"/><ref>http://www.jharkhand.gov.in/documents/10179/54299/List%20Of%20Caste%20And%20SubCast%20under%20CNT%20ACT</ref>
==Society== The Mal Paharias who live in the southern hills of [[Damin-i-koh]] and in the south and east of [[Santhal Parganas]] have been Hinduised. Among themselves they speak a corrupt form of Bengali, but with others they speak Bengali and Hindi. The Bengali and Devenagari scripts are used by them. The Mal Paharias survive on agriculture and forest produce, Rice is their staple food. Pulses like moong, masur, Kulthi and lar are consumed. They are non-vegetarians, but do not eat beef. Both men and women drink liquor, which may be home-made or bought from the market. They smoke indigenous cheroots, and chew tobacco mixed with lime (khaini) and betel.<ref>Houlton, Sir John, Bihar, the Heart of India, p. 81, Orient Longmans, 1949</ref><ref>{{cite web|url = http://tribesindia.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=368&Itemid=104&lang=en | title = Mal Paharia Adivasi |publisher = tribesindia.com |accessdate = }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url = http://jharkhandi.com/malpaharia.aspx | title = Mal Paharia Adivasi |publisher = jharkhand org |accessdate = }}</ref> ==See also==
* [[Mal (caste)|Mal People]]
